Can we identify the subtypes of the memory cells?

.file <- "result/step3/memory.rds"

if.needed(.file, {

    .batches <- data.table(tag = readLines(.memory.data$col))
    .batches[, c("barcode","batch") := tstrsplit(tag, "_")]

    .bbknn <- rcpp_mmutil_bbknn_pca(.memory.data$mtx,
                                    .batches$batch,
                                    knn = 30, RANK = 30,
                                    EM_ITER = 20,
                                    TAKE_LN = TRUE,
                                    NUM_THREADS = 8)
    saveRDS(.bbknn, .file)
})
.bbknn <- readRDS(.file)

1. Take CD markers and marker genes to classify subtype identities

.read.marker.file <- function(.file){
    x <- fread(.file, col.names=c("feat","ct"), header=F)
    .xx <- x[, .(feat=list(feat)), by = .(ct)];
    .ret <- .xx$feat; names(.ret) <- .xx$ct;
    .ret
}

.subtype.file <- "result/step3/assignment/round2.RDS"
.mkdir(dirname(.subtype.file))
if(!file.exists(.subtype.file)){
    .pos.markers <- .read.marker.file("marker/surface_round2_positive.txt")
    .neg.markers <- .read.marker.file("marker/surface_round2_negative.txt")
    .subtype.out <-
        rcpp_mmutil_annotate_columns(
            pos_labels = list(p1=.pos.markers),
            r_neg_labels = list(n1=.neg.markers),
            row_file = .memory.data$row,
            col_file = .memory.data$col,
            r_U = .bbknn$U,
            r_D = .bbknn$D,
            r_V = .bbknn$factors,
            EM_TOL = 1e-6,
            EM_ITER = 500)
    saveRDS(.subtype.out, .subtype.file)
}

.subtype.out <- readRDS(.subtype.file)

subtype.dt <-
    setDT(.subtype.out$annotation) %>%
    dplyr::rename(tag = col, subtype = argmax) %>%
    as.data.table()
.sub.show <- c("TH17","TH1/17","TH1","TH2")
.temp <- subtype.dt %>%
    left_join(annot.dt[, .(tag, celltype)])
plt <- plt.scatter.ct.2("mTconv", .temp, prot.raw.mtx)
print(plt)

.file <- fig.dir %&% "/Fig_round2_mTconv.pdf"
.gg.save(filename = .file, plot = plt, width=6, height=5)

2. Graph-based clustering

.file <- "result/step3/memory_bbknn_louvain.txt.gz"
.cells <- readLines(.memory.data$col)

if.needed(.file, {
    .bbknn.umap <- run.bbknn.umap(.bbknn, .cells, spread=5)
    fwrite(.bbknn.umap, .file)
})

.bbknn.umap <- fread(.file)

.size <- .bbknn.umap[, .(.N), by = .(membership)]
.valid <- .size[`N` >= 10, ]$membership
K <- length(.valid)

.bbknn.umap[, membership := as.character(`membership`)]
.bbknn.umap[!(membership %in% .valid), membership := "NA"]
.bbknn.umap[, membership := factor(`membership`, c(.valid, "NA"), 1:(K+1))]
K <- length(unique(.bbknn.umap$membership))

.show <- .bbknn.umap[membership != K] %>%
    left_join(annot.dt[, .(tag, celltype.protein)]) %>%
    na.omit()

.dt <- .show[, .(umap1 = median(umap1),
                 umap2 = median(umap2)),
             by = .(membership)]
plt <-
    .gg.plot(.show, aes(umap1, umap2, color=membership)) +
    xlab("UMAP 1") + ylab("UMAP 2") +
    ggrastr::rasterise(geom_point(stroke = .1, size = 1), dpi=300) +
    geom_point(data=.dt, size=3, color=2, pch=3) +
    geom_text(aes(label = `membership`), data=.dt, size=4, color="black") +
    scale_color_manual(values = .more.colors(K, nc.pal=10), guide="none")
print(plt)

.file <- fig.dir %&% "/Fig_memory_bbknn_umap_membership.pdf"
.gg.save(filename = .file, plot = plt, width=5, height=4)

3. Can we refine subtype assignments with clustering results?

.file <- "result/step3/memory_bbknn_louvain.txt.gz"
.bbknn.umap <- fread(.file)

.celltype.subtype <- 
    .bbknn.umap %>%
    left_join(subtype.dt) %>%
    left_join(annot.dt[, .(tag, celltype)]) %>%
    as.data.table()

.sub.mem <- .celltype.subtype[, .(nc = .N),
                              by = .(subtype, celltype, membership)]
.sub.mem[, ntot := sum(`nc`), by = .(membership)]
.sub.mem[, pr := `nc`/`ntot`]
.df <- 
    .sub.mem %>%
    mutate(row = celltype %&% "_" %&% subtype, col = membership,
           weight = logit(pmax(pmin(pr, 1-1e-2), 1e-2))) %>% 
    order.pair(ret.tab = TRUE)

plt <-
    .gg.plot(.df, aes(col, row, fill=weight, size = pmin(`nc`, 800))) +
    xlab("Louvain clustering") +
    ylab("cell type estimation by marker proteins/genes") +
    facet_grid(celltype ~ ., scales = "free", space = "free") +
    theme(legend.position = "bottom") +
    geom_point(pch=22) +
    scale_size_continuous("#cells", range=c(0,5)) +
    scale_fill_distiller("proportion",
                         palette="PuRd", direction = 1,
                         labels=function(x) round(sigmoid(x), 2))
print(plt)

.file <- fig.dir %&% "/Fig_bbknn_full_cluster.pdf"
.gg.save(filename = .file, plot = plt, width=5.5, height=4)

PDF

.valid.clust <- .sub.mem[order(pr, decreasing = T),
                         head(.SD, 1),
                         by = .(membership)]

.valid.celltype.cluster <-
    .valid.clust[pr > .3, .(membership, celltype, subtype)] %>%
    unique()

.celltype.subtype <- 
    .bbknn.umap %>%
    left_join(subtype.dt) %>%
    left_join(annot.dt[, .(tag, celltype)]) %>%
    as.data.table()

subtype.final <- 
    .celltype.subtype %>%
    rename(subtype.marker = subtype) %>% 
    (function(x) left_join(.valid.celltype.cluster, x)) %>%
    filter(subtype.marker == subtype) %>%
    na.omit() %>%
    as.data.table
.dt <- subtype.final[, .(umap1 = median(umap1),
                         umap2 = median(umap2)),
                     by = .(subtype, celltype)]

plt <-
    .gg.plot(subtype.final, aes(umap1, umap2, shape=celltype, fill=as.factor(subtype))) +
    xlab("UMAP 1") + ylab("UMAP 2") +
    ggrastr::rasterise(geom_point(stroke = .1, size = 1, alpha=.5), dpi=300) +
    scale_shape_manual(values = c(21,22), guide="none") +
    geom_text(aes(label = celltype %&% "-" %&% `subtype`), data=.dt, size=4, color="black", vjust=0, hjust=0) +
    scale_fill_brewer("subtype", palette = "Set3", guide="none")

print(plt)

.file <- fig.dir %&% "/Fig_memory_bbknn_umap_subtype.pdf"
.gg.save(filename = .file, plot = plt, width=4.5, height=4)
